• Making the USB installation disk from Linux

Download the Windows ISO file. Right click, Open With Disk Image Mounter.
It contains a file larger than 4 GB, too large for FAT32.

Format the USB disk with GPT.
Make a FAT32 partition. Copy to it all files in the ISO except ‘sources’
but including ‘sources/boot.wim’.
Make an NTFS partition. Copy to it all files in the ISO.

• Dual booting with Linux

Disable Fast Startup (or Linux might not detect some hardware).
Set the timezone to UTC (Windows sets the hardware clock to local time).
